http://www.thehindu.com/business/HCL-Tech-reverses-gear-ends-lower-post-Q2-numbers/article14006962.ece

Erasing all its early gains, shares of HCL Technologies on Tuesday ended lower as the company posted 0.2 per cent rise in consolidated net profit for the December quarter. The scrip of the software services major ended 0.58 per cent down at Rs. 838.50 on BSE. During the day, it had gained 3.17 per cent to Rs. 870.15, but lost ground on emergence of profit-booking.On NSE, the stock lost 0.48 per cent to settle at Rs. 838.25. Volume-wise, 3.33 lakh shares of the company changed hands at BSE and over 53 lakh at NSE during the day. “HCLT’s results were lower than expectations. Margins continue to reflect profitability challenges faced by HCLT in a bid to sustain high growth,” Kotak Securities senior vice-president and head, private client group research, Dipen Shah said.HCL Technologies on Tuesday posted 0.2 per cent rise in consolidated net profit at Rs. 1,920 crore for the December quarter, impacted by investments made on new generation technologies. The company, which follows July-June fiscal year, had posted a net profit of Rs. 1,915 crore in the year-ago period.It saw a growth of 11.4 per cent in revenue at Rs. 10,341 crore in the said quarter, from Rs. 9,283 crore a year ago. In dollar terms, the company’s net profit declined 5.4 per cent to $290.8 million in the reported quarter while revenues grew 5.1 per cent to $1.56 billion.